          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript used in private or public recitation and prayer in praise of the Hindu goddess Śītalā, the matron-deity presiding over smallpox. Reciting the text offers relief for fever, sick children, and other kinds of afflictions.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="san">In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Śītalāṣṭakastotra</title>
              <title type="vernacular">शीतलाष्टकस्तोत्र</title>
              <respStmt>
                <resp>scribe</resp>
                <persName type="authority">Sāṭhe, Moreśvara</persName>
              </respStmt>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrīskaṃdapurāṇe śītalāṣṭakaṃ stotraṃ saṃpūrṇaṃ // cha // śrīśītalādevyainamana idaṃ pustakaṃ moreśvarasāṭhe ity upanāmakena // (f. 1v).</colophon>
            </msItem>
